xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>14152</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-0048</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-0048.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Deductive system</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2022</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>25</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A deductive system <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is given by a type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> of “objects”, and for every pair <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B\in \mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {D}}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:em>morphisms</fr:em>, together with cut and identity laws:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li><fr:strong>cut:</fr:strong> for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B,C\in \mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
